snippet.textDisplay: So looking at the complete scoreboard what I can conclude for the whole group is Michael is good at free shots and Toast and Poki are good at aiming while Lily is kind of average at both (aka kinda good at aiming and kinda good at free shots kinda makes sense for a person dat is already has a foundation in in archery aka its her second time) meanwhile Toast hasnt had a single dead shot is he rly new at this LMAO ? Same about Pokemain WUT!! Toast & Poki are monstrously  good at adapting xD!  Meanwhile Scarra seems to be kind of the opposite altho he is a fast learner instead it seems oof... Fed and Michael tho oof oof... they are having rly hard time getting distracted it seems  especially Fed was getting frustrated each time he was shooting his release was rly stiff each shot when he was aiming and Michael I havent rly payd attention to him but he also seems to just be in his own world and try to adjust by his own standards not listening to advice at all (altho dat may just be me thinking dat cuz this is a video and in videos its hard to read into persons cuz the camera really captures a fraction of the atmosphere of the real situation most of the time ^^ but I gotta say after thinking about it a little Michael seems more like a trial and error sort of person you see how his score fluctuates beteen possitive and negative constantly this means he has readjusted (purposely or by accident every single time) So he was rly trying to achieve the main objective :P

Same about Pokemain WUT!! Toast & Poki are monstrously  good at adapting xD!  Meanwhile Scarra seems to be kind of the opposite altho he is a fast learner instead it seems oof... Fed and Michael tho oof oof... they are having rly hard time getting distracted it seems  especially Fed was getting frustrated each time he was shooting his release was rly stiff each shot when he was aiming and Michael I havent rly payd attention to him but he also seems to just be in his own world and try to adjust by his own standards not listening to advice at all (altho dat may just be me thinking dat cuz this is a video and in videos its hard to read into persons cuz the camera really captures a fraction of the atmosphere of the real situation most of the time ^^ but I gotta say after thinking about it a little Michael seems more like a trial and error sort of person you see how his score fluctuates beteen possitive and negative constantly this means he has readjusted (purposely or by accident every single time) So he was rly trying to achieve the main objective :P
